tr: a reflex that closes and opens the eyes rapidly

example: The TV announcer never seems to blink

tr: force to go away by blinking

value.def: When you blink or when you blink your eyes, you shut your eyes and very quickly open them again.

example.ex: Kathryn blinked and forced  a smile...
example.tran: 凯瑟琳眨了眨眼睛，挤出一丝微笑。

example.ex: She was blinking her eyes rapidly...

example.tran: 他眼睛飞快地眨个不停。

value.def: When a light blinks, it flashes on and off.

example.ex: Green and yellow lights blinked on the surface of the harbour...
example.tran: 海港的水面上闪烁着绿色和黄色的灯光。

example.ex: ...the blinking lights at the top of the Tutweiler Hotel.
example.tran: 塔特怀勒酒店楼顶闪烁的灯光

value.def: If you say that something happens in the blink of an eye, you mean that it happens very quickly.

example.ex: It was all over in the blink of an eye.
example.tran: 转眼之间，一切都结束了。

value.tran: 一眨眼的工夫；转眼之间；瞬间

value.def: If a machine goes on the blink, it stops working properly.

example.ex: ...an old TV that's on the blink.

value.tran: （机器）不能正常工作，出故障，出毛病

trans: （机器）不能正常工作，出故障，出毛病
字元闪烁；字符闪耀；字符闪烁
